data.title: Gus Garrick in costume.
data.meta_description:
Photograph of Gus Garrick wearing long pigtails and a white dress with a model bird attached to his hat, standing looking at viewer.

Gus Garrick was an actor who appeared at the Cambridge Theatre of Varieties in 1898, in Leeds in 1900, and in Sunderland in November 1914; he is also one of the people portrayed in Walter Lambert's painting 'Popularity' at the Museum of London (190-).
